summary: Southampton suffered a disappointing 0-3 home defeat against Manchester United in the Premier League. Marcus Rashford broke his scoring drought, netting United's first goal since March, followed by goals from Bruno Fernandes and Alejandro Garnacho. Southampton had been reduced to 10 men in the second half after Duje Caleta-Car received his second yellow card. The match saw Manchester United secure a much-needed win, while Southampton's struggles continued.

name: Man City
summary: Manchester City, a prominent Premier League club, faces a crucial hearing on Monday, March 6, where they will respond to 115 charges brought against them by the league. The case, often referred to as the "Trial of the Century," stems from allegations of financial irregularities and breaches of financial fair play regulations. The hearing will delve into various questions surrounding the club's ownership, player spending, and compliance with league rules. The outcome could have significant implications for Manchester City, potentially leading to sanctions such as point deductions, fines, or even exclusion from the Premier League.

name: EFL Cup
summary: The third round of the Carabao Cup, also known as the EFL Cup, concluded on Tuesday with notable results. Preston North End emerged victorious over Fulham in a dramatic penalty shootout, while Manchester United and Southampton secured comfortable wins. The fourth round draw will take place soon, but the exact date and time have yet to be announced. Fans can expect exciting fixtures and surprises as the competition progresses. In related news, the third round featured several intriguing matches, with Sheffield Wednesday defeating Blackpool and Manchester United facing Barnsley on September 18th. Sky Sports+ offers comprehensive coverage of the Carabao Cup, providing match schedules, fixtures, and streaming options.

name: New XEC Covid variant
summary: The new XEC variant of COVID-19 is spreading rapidly across Europe and the US, raising concerns among health experts. The variant, which is believed to be more transmissible than previous strains, has been detected in several countries and is expected to become dominant in the coming weeks. Symptoms of the XEC variant include sore throat, runny nose, fatigue, sneezing, and headache. Experts warn that the variant could spread rapidly during the autumn and winter months when people spend more time indoors. They recommend staying up-to-date with vaccinations, wearing masks in crowded areas, and practicing good hygiene measures to reduce the risk of infection.
